         <div type="edition" xml:lang="x-oldcham-Latn">
           <p>
             <lb n="1"/>di śakarāja <num value="977">977</num> nan· kāla Iśvaramūrtti sidaḥ yām̃ po ku śrī parameśvaravarmmadeva santā<lb
             n="2" break="no"/>na Uroja ya cakravarttirāja di nagara campa nim̃ ra pratiṣṭhā yām̃ vihāra rājakula niy· mulaṅ·
             <lb n="3"/>tra ra paralap· kalañ· ya ruṅ· nan· jeṅ· Avista bharuv· ra vuḥ Urām̃ maddan· lumvauv· kravāv· hu<lb
             n="4" break="no"/>mā ṅan· samasta Upakaraṇa tuy· devārccaṇa panūjā devatā nim̃ sadā kāla nau<g type="ddandaPlain">.</g>
           </p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
           <listApp>
             <app loc="3">
               <lem>ruṅ</lem>
               <rdg source="bib:Coedes1912_01">sāṅ</rdg>
            </app>
            <app loc="3">
              <lem>bharuv</lem>
              <rdg source="bib:Coedes1912_01"><unclear cert="low">ga sāv</unclear></rdg>
           </app>
               </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="fra">
           <p n="1-4">Dans <supplied reason="subaudible">l’année du</supplied> roi des <foreign>Śaka</foreign> 977. Ce fut le temps où cette manifestation d’Īśvara, le <foreign>Y.P.K. Śrī</foreign> Parameśvaradeva, de la famille d’Uroja, lequel fut roi universel dans ce pays de Campā, refonda le dieu de ce monastère de la famille royale. Il applattit <supplied reason="subaudible">le terrain pour</supplied> cette tour en pavillon, pour que tout soit <supplied reason="subaudible">fait</supplied> neuf. Il donna des esclaves avec des bovidés, des buffles, des rizières, et tous les ustensils <supplied reason="explanation">upakaraṇa</supplied> selon le culte, la vénération des dieux, maintenant <supplied reason="explanation">nim̃</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">et</supplied> toujours en avenir.</p>
         </div>
        <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
          <p n="1-4">
            In <supplied reason="subaudible">the year of the</supplied> <foreign>Śaka</foreign>-king 977: this was the time that this manifestation of Īśvara, milord <foreign>Śrī</foreign> Parameśvaradeva, of the lineage of Uroja, who was universal king in this land of Campā, re-established the deity of the monastery of the royal family. He flattened <supplied reason="subaudible">the ground for</supplied> this tower which is pavilion, in order that everything be new. He gave slaves with cows, buffaloes, rice fields, and all utensils <supplied reason="explanation">upakaraṇa</supplied> according to the cult, the worship of the gods, nows <supplied reason="explanation">nim̃</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">and</supplied> always in the future.
          </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
         </div>
